1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
 Thank you, Kelly.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:03,000
 Thank you, Kelly.

3
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:09,800
 So the first few years after college,

4
00:00:09,800 --> 00:00:12,400
 I attended a small group at my church at that time

5
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:15,120
 that was pretty multi-generation.

6
00:00:15,120 --> 00:00:16,840
 And one of the things that I appreciate

7
00:00:16,840 --> 00:00:20,000
 as an early 20-plus year or so in that group

8
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,480
 is that I got to hear about different parenting

9
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:25,040
 stories and experience within the group,

10
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:27,120
 from younger parents with little kids

11
00:00:27,120 --> 00:00:30,520
 to older couples with adult children.

12
00:00:30,520 --> 00:00:31,840
 And during my time in that group,

13
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:33,760
 one of the older ladies, who also

14
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:36,680
 happened to be the pastor's mom, she

15
00:00:36,680 --> 00:00:38,680
 would always ask the group to pray

16
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:43,040
 for her other adult child who had left the church.

17
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:44,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

18
00:00:44,480 --> 00:01:11,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

19
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:13,080
 And so those moments made me start

20
00:01:13,080 --> 00:01:16,600
 to wonder, how is faith being passed down

21
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:19,800
 from one generation to another?

22
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:21,760
 Looking at my own family, I think

23
00:01:21,760 --> 00:01:24,400
 we are blessed enough that me and all my siblings

24
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:27,960
 are still walking with the Lord as adults now.

25
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:30,920
 But how big of a role do parents play in this?

26
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:33,880
 And how much responsibility do adult children

27
00:01:33,880 --> 00:01:38,280
 have when it comes to keeping their parents' faith?

28
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:39,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

29
00:01:39,480 --> 00:02:06,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

30
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:08,800
 Today, we are going to continue with our series

31
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:10,000
 in the Book of Judges.

32
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,000
 And specifically, we are going to look

33
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,680
 at how each generation of Israel, after Joshua,

34
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:19,640
 they slowly loses their identity as God's chosen people

35
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:22,760
 and forsake the faith of their ancestor.

36
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:25,440
 Even though Israel was supposed to be a kingdom of priests

37
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:27,760
 and a holy nation for the Lord, they

38
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:30,920
 ended up becoming like the rest of the idolatrous nation

39
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,320
 around them.

40
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:57,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

41
00:02:57,960 --> 00:03:00,520
 So in my last sermon, we look at Judges 1,

42
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:02,800
 where the 12 tribes of Israel, they

43
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:05,760
 began to settle into their allotted territory

44
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:07,320
 in the promised land.

45
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:10,800
 And so their main task at this stage of the conquest

46
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:13,840
 was to drive out the remaining Canaanites who still live

47
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:17,160
 in the land in order to avoid their idol worship

48
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:20,160
 and also their moral corruption as Israel slowly

49
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:22,240
 settling into this land.

50
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:45,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

51
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:48,040
 However, as we see in Judges 1, Israel

52
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:50,680
 settled for half-hearted obedience,

53
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:53,400
 as they did not fully drive out all the Canaanites

54
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:56,080
 as the Lord has commanded them to.

55
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:57,960
 And even worse, they ended up making

56
00:03:57,960 --> 00:04:02,160
 covenants with these Canaanites and worshipping their idols.

57
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:20,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

58
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:22,160
 And so if you recall from my last sermon,

59
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:25,760
 Judges begin with this sort of double introduction.

60
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:27,960
 The first introduction that we look at last time,

61
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:31,080
 it highlights Israel's incomplete and half-hearted

62
00:04:31,080 --> 00:04:34,800
 conquest, where they failed to drive out the Canaanites.

63
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,840
 And so in other words, this is an assessment

64
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:39,880
 of Israel's military and political failure.

65
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:56,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

66
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:57,840
 And the second introduction sections

67
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,680
 that we will be looking into today,

68
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:02,840
 it highlights Israel's incomplete and half-hearted

69
00:05:02,840 --> 00:05:04,000
 faith.

70
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,520
 It gives us an overview of what is

71
00:05:05,520 --> 00:05:08,420
 about to happen in this main section of the book.

72
00:05:08,420 --> 00:05:11,520
 And it also introduces to the very important cycle

73
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:14,120
 of Israel's spiritual failure.

74
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:29,520
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

75
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,920
 So this morning, we will dive into the second introduction

76
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:35,040
 section, and we will explore these questions together.

77
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:38,040
 What does enduring faith that lasts through generations

78
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:40,240
 requires of us?

79
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:42,400
 How do we keep ourselves from falling

80
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:45,480
 into the same situation as this judges' generations,

81
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:48,360
 where each generation after each generation,

82
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:51,000
 they just fall further and further away

83
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,120
 from the faith of their ancestors?

84
00:05:53,120 --> 00:06:07,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

85
00:06:07,760 --> 00:06:09,920
 And so we will answer these questions from our passage

86
00:06:09,920 --> 00:06:10,420
 today.

87
00:06:10,420 --> 00:06:12,320
 And if you have your own Bible, you're

88
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:16,480
 welcome to go to Judges 2 and follow along.

89
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:21,680
 And so first, enduring faith requires us to remember.

90
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:33,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

91
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:36,800
 And so Judges 2, especially in verse 7,

92
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,800
 it restates the very important details

93
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:42,520
 about the generations before, that is the Joshua generation.

94
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:47,040
 They remain faithful and steadfast to the Lord.

95
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:57,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

96
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,720
 But when we come to verse 10, things actually

97
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:02,060
 take a pretty drastic turn.

98
00:07:02,060 --> 00:07:05,000
 We learn that after the whole Joshua generation had

99
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,160
 been gathered to their ancestors,

100
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,880
 another generation grew up who did not know the Lord

101
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:13,880
 or remember the things he had done for Israel.

102
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:24,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

103
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,800
 And so to put it another way, they

104
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:33,040
 forgot who Yahweh is and what he had done for their ancestors.

105
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:40,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

106
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:42,880
 And what is the result of their forgetfulness?

107
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:45,240
 We see this in the following three verses,

108
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:47,400
 so starting in 11.

109
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:50,600
 "Then the Israelites did evils in the eyes of the Lord

110
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,320
 and served the Baals.

111
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:55,120
 They pursued the Lord, the God of their ancestor,

112
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:57,400
 who had brought them out of Egypt.

113
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:59,400
 They followed and worshipped various gods

114
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:03,000
 of the peoples around them, and they aroused the Lord's anger.

115
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:07,920
 Because they pursued him and served Baal and Arcturus."

116
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:10,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

117
00:08:10,640 --> 00:08:12,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

118
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:41,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

119
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:43,360
 It is a little hard to notice this

120
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:45,640
 in the English or the Mandarin translation,

121
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:48,760
 but in the original Hebrew manuscripts, after verse 10,

122
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:51,160
 all these action verbs in the next three verse stages

123
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:55,160
 comes one after another to show the degree of Israel's

124
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:56,480
 apostasy.

125
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:59,120
 "They did evils in the eyes of the Lord.

126
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:01,080
 They pursued the Lord.

127
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:03,200
 They followed other gods.

128
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:06,080
 They worshipped the gods of the people around them.

129
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,600
 They angered the Lord.

130
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,840
 Then again, they pursued the Lord

131
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:12,920
 and served Baal and Arcturus."

132
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:15,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

133
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:42,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

134
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:47,280
 And so forgetfulness comes with consequences.

135
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:49,960
 I remember when I went to get my US driver's license,

136
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:52,680
 and at that point, I had been driving back in Malaysia

137
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:54,840
 for three parts a year already.

138
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:59,560
 So I signed up for a driving test, and I went to the DMV.

139
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

140
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:12,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

141
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:16,240
 And on that day, I was acing through the test.

142
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,280
 Vehicle check, done.

143
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:20,000
 Parallel part, done.

144
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,160
 Three-point turn, done.

145
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:24,320
 And then the proctor asked me to get on the street,

146
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:28,680
 and again, I cruised through it without any issues at all.

147
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:32,160
 And when we made our way back to the DMV after driving around,

148
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:34,080
 I was feeling pretty confident.

149
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:38,320
 And we came to this one last stop sign inside the DMV.

150
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:58,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

151
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:01,480
 And so you have to understand that in Malaysia,

152
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:04,840
 a stop sign is more like a suggestion.

153
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:06,760
 And so most drivers, they will slow down

154
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:08,200
 when they approach the stop signs.

155
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:11,520
 And if they don't see any pedestrians or any vehicles

156
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:15,620
 around, we will just continue on without coming to a full stop.

157
00:11:15,620 --> 00:11:19,880
 And so when I came to this final stop sign inside the DMV,

158
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:23,240
 I forgot that I was in a driving test.

159
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:25,240
 I allowed my old instinct to take over,

160
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:28,040
 and I just blew straight past the stop sign.

161
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:31,320
 And immediately, the proctor turned at me

162
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:33,560
 and pointed at the stop sign.

163
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:36,440
 And at that moment, I knew I wasn't going to pass.

164
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:38,560
 And so I ended up having to go back,

165
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:40,440
 experience through all the hassles of DMV

166
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:44,800
 again after a few weeks, just to redo my exam.

167
00:11:44,800 --> 00:12:14,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

168
00:12:14,760 --> 00:12:22,360
 And so in the same way, spiritual forgetfulness

169
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:26,360
 also comes with serious implications for our faith.

170
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:29,600
 When we forgot what the Lord has done for us,

171
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:32,200
 when we forget his commands for us,

172
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:35,680
 when we forget his grace and his mercy in our lives,

173
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:38,120
 we slowly lose our faith and allow

174
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:42,960
 our old self and sinful nature to take over our lives again.

175
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:58,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

176
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:01,720
 And so how do we counter this sort of spiritual forgetfulness

177
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:03,480
 or spiritual dementia?

178
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:05,800
 It is by remembering.

179
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:08,360
 Remembering is a common practice for God's people

180
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,600
 all throughout the generations.

181
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:18,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

182
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:20,480
 For example, in the Old Testament,

183
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:22,280
 the Passover was being instituted

184
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:25,240
 as an annual festival in the Jewish calendar

185
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:27,960
 so that all generations of Israels that comes after,

186
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:30,880
 they can remember what the Lord has done for them

187
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:34,280
 in the first Passover in Exodus by delivering them

188
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:36,560
 from slavery in Egypt.

189
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:44,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

190
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:45,680
 And when we come to the New Testament,

191
00:13:45,680 --> 00:13:47,560
 we also find other examples as well.

192
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:50,080
 The early church, they partake in the Lord's Supper

193
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:53,040
 or communion as a remembrance of what Jesus

194
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:55,560
 has done for them at the cross.

195
00:13:55,560 --> 00:14:01,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

196
00:14:01,040 --> 00:14:03,360
 And even today, believers all throughout the world

197
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:05,840
 partake in the sacraments of holy communion

198
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:09,160
 as well to remember the sacrifice of Jesus.

199
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:11,720
 And in fact, we just did that a few moments ago

200
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,640
 in our service.

201
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:24,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

202
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:27,760
 And therefore, remembering is a spiritual discipline

203
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:32,280
 that we should all practice so that our faith can be lasting.

204
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:42,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

205
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:44,840
 And so what does enduring faith requires of us?

206
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:47,520
 First, it requires us to remember,

207
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:51,080
 to remember who God is and what He has done for us.

208
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,800
 And this is the first lesson that we can

209
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:55,040
 learn from Israel's history here.

210
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:57,600
 And secondly, enduring faith requires

211
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:01,600
 us to actively repent and turn from our own ways.

212
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:16,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

213
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:19,360
 And so let's pick up our passage again from verse 14.

214
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:21,280
 "In His anger against Israel, the Lord

215
00:15:21,280 --> 00:15:24,440
 gave them into the hands of the raiders who plundered them.

216
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:27,520
 He sold them into the hands of the enemies all around whom

217
00:15:27,520 --> 00:15:30,160
 they were no longer able to resist.

218
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:31,960
 And whenever Israel went out to fight,

219
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:35,080
 the hand of the Lord was against them to defeat them.

220
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:40,160
 Just as He has sworn to them, they were in great distress."

221
00:15:40,160 --> 00:16:00,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

222
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:04,280
 And so when Israel abandoned the Lord and worshiped other idols,

223
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:07,000
 the Lord gave them into the hands of the oppressors,

224
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:10,480
 where Israel, they would suffer for a period of time.

225
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:18,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

226
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:20,320
 And then in verse 16, "Then the Lord

227
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:22,360
 raised up judges who saved them out

228
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:24,240
 of the hands of these raiders.

229
00:16:24,240 --> 00:16:26,800
 And yet they would not listen to their judges,

230
00:16:26,800 --> 00:16:30,240
 but prostitute themselves to other gods and worship them.

231
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:32,400
 They quickly turned from the ways of their ancestor

232
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:36,160
 who had been obedient to the Lord's command."

233
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:52,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

234
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,320
 And so what happened here?

235
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:56,880
 "When Israel suffered under the hand of the oppressors

236
00:16:56,880 --> 00:16:58,800
 and cried out to the Lord, the Lord

237
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:02,040
 would raise up judges to deliver them from their oppressions

238
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:03,640
 and sufferings."

239
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:11,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

240
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:14,280
 And who are these judges?

241
00:17:14,280 --> 00:17:17,200
 First, they are Israel's deliverer.

242
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:20,320
 But secondly, they also serve as a catalyst

243
00:17:20,320 --> 00:17:24,000
 for godly living among the people of God.

244
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:31,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

245
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:34,240
 But this is a very important but.

246
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:37,200
 Israel's disobedience-- Israel's obedience

247
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:39,120
 did not last long at all.

248
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:40,920
 Look at verse 17 again.

249
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:44,360
 It says, "Yet they would not listen to their judges,

250
00:17:44,360 --> 00:17:47,880
 but prostitute themselves to other gods and worship them.

251
00:17:47,880 --> 00:17:50,720
 They quickly turned from the ways of their ancestor

252
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:54,160
 who had been obedient to the Lord's command."

253
00:17:54,160 --> 00:18:05,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

254
00:18:05,080 --> 00:18:07,560
 And then in verse 18 and 19, again, we

255
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:10,880
 see the same pattern happening all over.

256
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,920
 "Whenever the Lord raised up a judge for them,

257
00:18:12,920 --> 00:18:15,000
 he was with the judge and saved them

258
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:17,000
 out of the hands of their enemies,

259
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:18,960
 as long as the judge lived.

260
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:21,080
 For the Lord relented because of their groaning

261
00:18:21,080 --> 00:18:24,080
 under those who oppressed and afflicted them.

262
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:26,120
 But when the judge died, the people

263
00:18:26,120 --> 00:18:28,680
 returned to ways even more corrupt

264
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:31,680
 than those of their ancestors, following other gods

265
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:34,160
 and serving and worshiping them.

266
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:36,440
 They refused to give up their evil practice

267
00:18:36,440 --> 00:18:38,640
 and stubborn ways."

268
00:18:38,640 --> 00:19:07,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

269
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:09,600
 And so even though the Lord would raise up judges

270
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:12,760
 to deliver Israel from their oppressions,

271
00:19:12,760 --> 00:19:14,400
 we learn that when the judge died,

272
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:17,160
 the people actually returned to ways even worse

273
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:19,040
 than their ancestors.

274
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:29,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

275
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:30,920
 And so think about it this way.

276
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:33,060
 The first time that you did something wrong,

277
00:19:33,060 --> 00:19:35,200
 it makes sense for mercy and forgiveness

278
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:37,880
 to be shown right because of various reasons.

279
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:41,000
 It can be because of ignorance, or it was just an accident,

280
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:42,640
 and so on.

281
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:46,000
 But when you repeat the same sin over and over again

282
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:49,080
 and show no signs of remorse and repentance,

283
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:51,380
 it just becomes like a cancerous disease

284
00:19:51,380 --> 00:19:56,000
 that slowly eats you away and corrupts your heart.

285
00:19:56,000 --> 00:20:14,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

286
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:17,720
 So this is what is happening to this judge's narration.

287
00:20:17,720 --> 00:20:21,640
 Verse 19 ends with a summary on this corrupted generation,

288
00:20:21,640 --> 00:20:24,760
 that they refused to give up their evil practice

289
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:26,920
 and stubborn ways.

290
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:29,920
 And because of the refusal to repent and turn

291
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:32,680
 from the evil ways, Israel just continues

292
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:36,120
 to spiral down into worse and worse apostasy.

293
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:39,440
 And this cycle of sinning, oppressions,

294
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:43,160
 crying out to the Lord, deliverance, peace,

295
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:44,960
 and then back to sinning again, it

296
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:49,200
 just keeps repeating itself with no end in sight.

297
00:20:49,200 --> 00:21:10,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

298
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:13,160
 And so how do we avoid the downfall of Israel here?

299
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:15,480
 The answer is simple, but to actually lift it out

300
00:21:15,480 --> 00:21:19,200
 actually requires a lot of intentionality on our end.

301
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:22,880
 We need to truly repent and turn from our evil ways.

302
00:21:22,880 --> 00:21:34,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

303
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:37,560
 And true repentance is not just a one-time event,

304
00:21:37,560 --> 00:21:41,320
 but it is a day-to-day, moment-by-moment practice.

305
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:45,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

306
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:48,080
 One metaphor that I find helpful to think

307
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,720
 about this practice of repentance

308
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:52,280
 is spiritual breathing.

309
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:55,920
 As long as we are alive, we never stop breathing, right?

310
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:59,240
 And so this is the same when it comes to spiritual breathing.

311
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:02,240
 We exhale by confessing our sin, knowing

312
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:07,160
 that Jesus has already taken away our sins at the cross.

313
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:10,240
 We then inhale by surrendering to God,

314
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:13,440
 turning from our own ways and turning back to him

315
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:17,920
 as the ultimate authority of our lives.

316
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:38,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

317
00:22:38,040 --> 00:22:40,520
 And so the more we are able to practice

318
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:42,880
 the spiritual discipline of repentance,

319
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:45,080
 and it becomes more nature to us,

320
00:22:45,080 --> 00:22:47,200
 the more we are able to align our lives

321
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:49,480
 with the heart of God.

322
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:55,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

323
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:58,440
 And so this is the second lesson we can learn from Israel

324
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:00,600
 when it comes to keeping our faith,

325
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:03,280
 that it requires us to truly repent and turn

326
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:05,880
 from our evil ways constantly.

327
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:09,040
 If not, our heart will quickly become hardened,

328
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:13,280
 and we fall further and further away from the Lord.

329
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:22,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

330
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:25,840
 And the third lesson that I want us to take away from our passage

331
00:23:25,840 --> 00:23:28,600
 today is that enduring faith requires

332
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:31,520
 us to acknowledge our own insufficiency

333
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:34,320
 and our need for a savior.

334
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:41,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

335
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:43,800
 And so I know we have been taking lessons

336
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:45,720
 from Israel's failure here, but I

337
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:48,120
 want to speak up for them here for a little bit.

338
00:23:48,120 --> 00:23:50,200
 A lot of time when we read scripture,

339
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,520
 we can be quick to label a certain characters

340
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:56,800
 or a group of people as just simply good or bad.

341
00:23:56,800 --> 00:24:00,320
 But when in fact, there's a lot more complexity to it,

342
00:24:00,320 --> 00:24:02,360
 and more often than not, we actually

343
00:24:02,360 --> 00:24:05,640
 share the same tendency as these characters as well.

344
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:28,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

345
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:31,800
 And when we look at this new generation of Israel

346
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:34,480
 after Joshua, all of them grew up

347
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:36,400
 wandering in the wilderness, right?

348
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:39,440
 This is the only way of living that they were familiar with.

349
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:41,360
 And so now that they have settled down

350
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:44,800
 into the promised land and own their own land,

351
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:47,640
 they had to pick up new skills in this new environment

352
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:50,600
 in order to survive, with agriculture being

353
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:53,080
 the primary mode of living here.

354
00:24:53,080 --> 00:25:04,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

355
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:06,960
 And so this is where the appeal of worshipping Baals and Ash

356
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:10,360
 Torres comes in, because their Canaanite neighbors believe

357
00:25:10,360 --> 00:25:14,000
 that these gods have the power to control rain, the storm,

358
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:15,080
 and fertility.

359
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:19,280
 And thus, they play an important role in an agrarian society.

360
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:21,520
 And so for this new generation of Israel,

361
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:23,920
 the way to survive in this new place

362
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:25,960
 is just to look around them and learn

363
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:29,240
 from their Canaanite neighbors, worshipping the storm and rain

364
00:25:29,240 --> 00:25:33,200
 gods with the hope that these gods will also bless them

365
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:35,680
 and give them good crops.

366
00:25:35,680 --> 00:25:58,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

367
00:25:58,480 --> 00:25:59,960
 And so from their perspective, this

368
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:02,160
 is actually a completely logical move.

369
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:05,000
 And we should not be quick to judge them

370
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,640
 without understanding the challenge they

371
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:08,560
 face in order to survive.

372
00:26:08,560 --> 00:26:14,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

373
00:26:14,760 --> 00:26:16,480
 Yet at the same time, we also have

374
00:26:16,480 --> 00:26:19,160
 to acknowledge that the biggest issue here

375
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:23,520
 is that they choose human logic over trusting God,

376
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:26,720
 the same God who provided for them even in the wilderness

377
00:26:26,720 --> 00:26:30,080
 and who will surely provide for them in the promised land

378
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:31,400
 as well.

379
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:43,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

380
00:26:43,760 --> 00:26:45,440
 And so in other words, they think

381
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:48,040
 that they know how to survive in this new environment

382
00:26:48,040 --> 00:26:50,840
 better than God, even though God has specifically

383
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:53,120
 commanded them time and time again

384
00:26:53,120 --> 00:26:55,800
 to not make covenant with the Canaanites,

385
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:58,800
 or else they will be tempted to follow the detestable things

386
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:03,120
 they do in their idols' worship and sin against the Lord.

387
00:27:03,120 --> 00:27:15,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

388
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:18,240
 And so as a result of their incomplete faith,

389
00:27:18,240 --> 00:27:21,120
 we see that in verse 20, "Therefore, the Lord

390
00:27:21,120 --> 00:27:23,960
 was very angry with Israel and said,

391
00:27:23,960 --> 00:27:26,400
 because this nation has violated the covenant I

392
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:30,320
 ordain for their ancestor and has not listened to me,

393
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:33,320
 I will no longer drive out before them any of the nations

394
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:35,520
 Joshua left when he died.

395
00:27:35,520 --> 00:27:37,720
 I will use them to test Israel and see

396
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:39,960
 whether they will keep the way of the Lord

397
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:43,120
 and walk in it as their ancestors did.

398
00:27:43,120 --> 00:27:45,400
 The Lord had allowed those nations to remain.

399
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:47,960
 He did not drive them out at once by giving them

400
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:49,880
 to the hands of Joshua."

401
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:53,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

402
00:27:53,360 --> 00:28:19,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

403
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:23,960
 So this is the predicament that Israel found themselves in.

404
00:28:23,960 --> 00:28:26,040
 As we look at the stories of all the judges

405
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:28,960
 in the rest of the book, none of them

406
00:28:28,960 --> 00:28:32,520
 were able to put an end to the cycles of spiritual downfall

407
00:28:32,520 --> 00:28:36,520
 and moral corruptions that Israel found themselves in.

408
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:40,440
 And this pattern of sin, oppression, crying out,

409
00:28:40,440 --> 00:28:44,080
 deliverance, peace, and then back to sinning again,

410
00:28:44,080 --> 00:28:47,400
 it just keeps on repeating itself.

411
00:28:47,400 --> 00:29:07,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

412
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:10,400
 And if you think you can find a happy ending by flipping

413
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:13,480
 to the end of the Book of Judges,

414
00:29:13,480 --> 00:29:16,640
 you will actually find the complete opposite.

415
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:18,440
 In the last few chapters of Judges,

416
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:21,000
 Israel descends into utter chaos,

417
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:23,760
 and the book actually ends with this remark.

418
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:26,360
 "In those days, there was no kings in Israel.

419
00:29:26,360 --> 00:29:29,880
 Everyone did what was right in their own eyes."

420
00:29:29,880 --> 00:29:44,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

421
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:48,720
 So where is our hope in all of this?

422
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:51,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

423
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:53,160
 I like how this scholar has put it.

424
00:29:53,160 --> 00:29:57,040
 He says, "God's covenant with Israel as a contract

425
00:29:57,040 --> 00:29:59,600
 is broken because of Israel's apostasy,

426
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:01,080
 that is, Israel's failure to hold out

427
00:30:01,080 --> 00:30:03,080
 the ends of the obligation.

428
00:30:03,080 --> 00:30:06,320
 But this covenant as a promise still stands,

429
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:09,160
 that is, God's promise to his people.

430
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:10,720
 What is needed for its fulfillment

431
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:15,000
 is an Israel which does not fail to keep its obligation.

432
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:17,160
 And in the New Testament terms, this fulfillment

433
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:20,560
 comes in Jesus, the Messiah, who is everything

434
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:23,800
 that Israel should have been but was not,

435
00:30:23,800 --> 00:30:26,640
 the perfectly obedient Israel.

436
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:29,800
 And this is where our hope can be found.

437
00:30:29,800 --> 00:30:54,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

438
00:30:54,760 --> 00:30:57,040
 And so like the Israel who wandered in the wilderness

439
00:30:57,040 --> 00:31:00,360
 for 40 years, Jesus spent 40 days and 40 nights

440
00:31:00,360 --> 00:31:03,920
 in the wilderness, and he was being tempted by the Satan.

441
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:06,440
 And yet he did not sin.

442
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:13,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

443
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:16,000
 And like Israel who receives the Torah from the Lord

444
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:18,000
 and that tells them how they ought

445
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:20,520
 to live as God's covenant people,

446
00:31:20,520 --> 00:31:23,080
 and yet they fail to live up to it,

447
00:31:23,080 --> 00:31:26,720
 Jesus himself is the Word of God who became flesh.

448
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:28,680
 And he shows us the true and better way

449
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:32,360
 of living by redefining what true and better righteousness

450
00:31:32,360 --> 00:31:33,480
 means.

451
00:31:33,480 --> 00:31:51,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

452
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:54,720
 And so where Israel fails, Jesus remains perfectly

453
00:31:54,720 --> 00:31:56,920
 faithful and obedient.

454
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:59,640
 And that is why he is our ultimate hope.

455
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:05,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

456
00:32:05,760 --> 00:32:08,280
 And so this is our third and final lesson from Judges 2

457
00:32:08,280 --> 00:32:08,920
 here.

458
00:32:08,920 --> 00:32:12,400
 Enduring faith requires us to acknowledge our inability

459
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:15,000
 to save ourselves like the Israelites,

460
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:18,160
 and then also realizing that we need a Savior, that

461
00:32:18,160 --> 00:32:20,320
 is Jesus himself.

462
00:32:20,320 --> 00:32:29,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

463
00:32:29,800 --> 00:32:33,200
 And this is the first and the most important steps.

464
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:36,440
 Once we realize our own human depravity and our need

465
00:32:36,440 --> 00:32:40,520
 for Jesus, we then repent and turn from our evil ways

466
00:32:40,520 --> 00:32:43,200
 to follow the ways of Jesus, allowing

467
00:32:43,200 --> 00:32:47,240
 this practice of repentance to become part of our daily lives.

468
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:49,880
 And as we walk through the rest of our faith journey,

469
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:52,840
 we also take the time to reflect on who God is

470
00:32:52,840 --> 00:32:55,960
 and remember his gift of salvation, of grace

471
00:32:55,960 --> 00:32:58,320
 and mercy in our life.

472
00:32:58,320 --> 00:33:21,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

473
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:22,960
 So let's pray together.

474
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:24,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

475
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:28,440
 Heavenly Father, as we enter into this season of Advent,

476
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:31,840
 we want to take some time to reflect and remember

477
00:33:31,840 --> 00:33:34,280
 your gift of salvation.

478
00:33:34,280 --> 00:33:37,120
 Thank you that you did not leave us in our own mess,

479
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:39,280
 but you sent your only son, Jesus,

480
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:42,160
 to die on the cross for us.

481
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:59,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

482
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:04,240
 Jesus, you are Emmanuel, God with us.

483
00:34:04,240 --> 00:34:06,760
 Thank you for being with us in our brokenness

484
00:34:06,760 --> 00:34:08,760
 and our suffering.

485
00:34:08,760 --> 00:34:11,680
 You are the founder and perfecter of our faith.

486
00:34:11,680 --> 00:34:14,320
 And for the joy that lay before you,

487
00:34:14,320 --> 00:34:17,920
 you endured the cross, despising its shame,

488
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:21,760
 and sat down at the right hand of the throne of God.

489
00:34:21,760 --> 00:34:22,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

490
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:51,560
 And Holy Spirit, you are God within us.

491
00:34:51,560 --> 00:34:55,800
 Thank you for dwelling in us and grant us the power

492
00:34:55,800 --> 00:34:58,560
 to live a life of active repentance

493
00:34:58,560 --> 00:35:02,360
 so that our faith is active and living.

494
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:18,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

495
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:20,480
 And in your most precious name, we pray.

496
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:21,160
 Amen.

497
00:35:21,160 --> 00:35:23,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

498
00:35:23,160 --> 00:35:24,720
 Amen.

499
00:35:24,720 --> 00:35:25,960
 All right, thank you, Nhu-Vy.

500
00:35:25,960 --> 00:35:28,040
 Thank you all for joining us.

501
00:35:28,040 --> 00:35:29,640
 You are dismissed.

502
00:35:29,640 --> 00:35:30,560
 So go in peace.

503
00:35:30,560 --> 00:35:31,720
 You are loved.

504
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:34,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

505
00:35:34,280 --> 00:35:37,640
 [MUSIC PLAYING]

506
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:39,640
 (music)

